<plot>During China's 1920s Republican Period, warlords carve out personal fiefdoms across the country and impose self-serving laws with the barrel of a gun. Into this anarchy rides a masked feminine Zorro, nom de guerre Violet (Angela Mao), to do battle, right wrongs and foment rebellion against the most corrupt and brutal warlord of all, Tung Ta-Chou (Chui Fook Sang). Unbeknownst to Tung, however, Violet is his own daughter. Tung orders his psycho enforcer Master Wu (Yi Chang) to track down and dispose of this pesky rebel queen. Meanwhile, Violet begins a flirtation with an attractive stranger (Tien Peng) who comes to town with the other half of a treasure map held by Tung. Ultimately, Master Wu betrays the warlord on the lure of the complete treasure map, enabling Violet and the stranger to apprehend Master Wu and beat the warlord at his own game.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?334923</url></doc>
